#Loading the dataset from the prostate_cancer.csv file for analysis
dataset = read.csv("/Users/ruchitamaheshkumar/Desktop/prostate_cancer.csv", header = T)
#Store the value of the PSA which will be response variable 
y = dataset$psa
CollectionData = read.csv("/Users/ruchitamaheshkumar/Desktop/prostate_cancer.csv", header = T)
psa = CollectionData[,2]
cancervol = CollectionData[,3]
weight = CollectionData[,4]
age = CollectionData[,5]
benpros = CollectionData[,6]
vesinv = CollectionData[,7]
capspen = CollectionData[,8]
gleason = CollectionData[,9]

hist(psa,xlab="PSA Level",main="HISTOGRAM OF PSA LEVEL",col="yellow", breaks=20)

boxplot(log(psa))

# 1. Histogram of each variable using single for loop
for (i in 1:9) {
 hist(CollectionData[,i], xlab=colnames(CollectionData)[i],
 main=paste("Histogram of",colnames(CollectionData[i])),
col="red",breaks=20)
 }

#Storing the value of predictor variables 
cancervol_data = dataset$cancervol 
weight_data = dataset$weight 
age_data = dataset$age

benpros_data = dataset$benpros 
vesinv_data = factor(dataset$vesinv) 
capsen_data = dataset$capspen 
gleason_data = dataset$gleason

#Create a linear regression model using lm function the response variable and 
prostate.model = lm(y~cancervol_data + weight_data + age_data + benpros_data + vesinv_data + capsen_data + gleason_data)


#plotting fitted y values vs residuals values
plot(fitted(prostate.model), resid(prostate.model), main = "Fitted values VS Residuals values of model",ylab="residuals",xlab = "fitted value")
abline(h=0)

#checking normality of residuals plot
qqnorm(resid(prostate.model), main = "Residuals of Linear Regression Model") 
qqline(resid(prostate.model))

#time series plot
plot(resid(prostate.model), type = 'l', main = "Time series of Residuals") 
abline(h=0)

#creating new model with log transform of response as the regular model residuals have # deviation form normality and not evenly scattered around zero.
prostate.model.log = lm(log(y)~cancervol_data + weight_data + age_data + benpros_data + vesinv_data + capsen_data + gleason_data)

#plotting fitted y against residuals
plot(fitted(prostate.model.log), resid(prostate.model.log), main = "Fitted values VS Residuals values")
abline(h=0)

#checking normality of residuals
qqnorm(resid(prostate.model.log), main = "Log transformed Linear Regression Model") 
qqline(resid(prostate.model.log))

#time series
plot(resid(prostate.model.log), type = 'l', main = "Time series of Residuals") 
abline(h=0)

# Ftest will be used to test the model significance # use the summary function on the log model summary(prostate.model.log)
summary(prostate.model.log)

#we reduce the model and create the model only these models. 
prostate.model.log.reduced = lm(log(y)~cancervol_data + benpros_data + vesinv_data + gleason_data)

#plotting fitted y against residuals for reduced model 
plot(fitted(prostate.model.log.reduced), resid(prostate.model.log.reduced), main = "Fitted values VS Residuals values")
abline(h=0)

#checking normality of residuals for reduced model 
qqnorm(resid(prostate.model.log.reduced), main = "Log transformed Reduced Linear Regression Model")
qqline(resid(prostate.model.log.reduced))

#time series
plot(resid(prostate.model.log.reduced), type = 'l', main = "Time series of Residuals") 
abline(h=0)

anova(prostate.model.log.reduced, prostate.model.log)
